      <title>Re: Test template works, but mine not :(</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezfire/forum/general/test_template_works_but_mine_not/re_test_template_works_but_mine_not</link>
      <description>I've seen this - I'm not sure why it happens since the path to your pear libraries should be in your path... but it fails for some reason - so far randomly.&#13;
&#13;
Try adding:&#13;
&#13;
if (!class_exists( "FirePHP" ))&#13;
   require_once ('/usr/share/php/FirePHPCore/FirePHP.class.php');&#13;
&#13;
on line 27 (between the comments and the class definition) of extension/ezfire/classes/ezfire.php.  Make sure the require_once is pointing to the correct path.&#13;
&#13;
Let me know if that works and I'll add it.&#13;
&#13;
Edit: added the "Make sure" part.</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Steven E Bailey)</author>
