    <item>
      <title>A few remarks</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezfire/forum/general/a_few_remarks</link>
      <description>First, congratulations and thank you for this extension. I have briefly tested it, and I must say I like it :-)&#13;
&#13;
Now a few remarks ;-)&#13;
&#13;
With XDebug enabled, you get a notice on the undefined variable $new when going to  ezfire/firetest. If you initialize it, you then get an  undefined offset 1 from FirePHP itself.&#13;
&#13;
Also, note that the require_once on autoload.php is not required, as it is part of the eZ Publish controller, or the file will never be reached.&#13;
&#13;
To conclude, maybe it would be cool to add some text on ezfire/firetest that gives some example of how the extension is used, as it is most likely that this is the first thing people will do when first trying the extension. I know fore sure I did do this.</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Bertrand Dunogier)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezfire/forum/general/a_few_remarks</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 09 May 2011 08:52:06 +0000</pubDate>
