    <item>
      <title>Re: relation to the fireez extension?</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezfire/forum/general/relation_to_the_fireez_extension/re_relation_to_the_fireez_extension</link>
      <description>Well, I think that the person doing the fireez extension wanted to use the same method to display stuff as the firephp extension - using the multi-part capabilities of firefox to send additional information to the firebug console in the headers.  Which might be a way to go and maybe even a way to get more precise information (for instance the line number capabilities of firephp will always return the line number where it is being displayed in the ezfire extension).&#13;
&#13;
But, I was keenly interested in firephp when it first came out and have been trying it out since then and this extension is the result of  refining that for the past 8 months or so.&#13;
&#13;
I saw the fireez extension too when it first came out and was interested in seeing how that would work out, but, as far as I can see nothing was ever developed.  The idea  there was primarily to display ezpublish error message in the console and while I did play around with that I don't find that very useful.  To get template variables in the firephp console has been useful as has the ability to dump output to a file to debug php code without having the debug output mixed in with all the other ezpublish debug messages. &#13;
&#13;
</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Steven E Bailey)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezfire/forum/general/relation_to_the_fireez_extension/re_relation_to_the_fireez_extension</guid>
